author: @stevel205
content:
The first time I saw the dancer drag her down the stage wearing high heels I was so impressed, doing that in heels!!

Then seeing the chair drag from other angles I wondered about safety and was looking for some sort of wheels or anti-tipping device.

This answers my question, the safety was practice and sometimes the acrobatics don't go to plan but no one looked hurt so a fun time had by all.

I love her infectious laugh, the real one.
